In article <jhesseCo0LG3.JuD@netcom.com>, John Hesse <jhesse@netcom.com> wrote:
>In article <strnlghtCnzJ79.74G@netcom.com>,
>David Sternlight <david@sternlight.com> wrote:
>>...
>>Prohibiting the manufacture and export of nuclear weapons to Saddam means
>>giving up some of our rights. The government has shown few or no cases where
>>he's dropped an atom bomb on us. Shouldn't we wait until New York or
>>Washington are lost beacause of a Saddam bomb before we give up rights?
>>
>
>This is such a stretch that it makes the opposite point.

To the contrary, it's a standard rhetorical technique called "reductio ad
absurdum". The parallel is intended to show the absurdity of the pure logic
behind the argument, by using the same logic with different circumstances.

David
